-- New Orleans Police Officers Sentenced for Post-Katrina Deaths
-- B y   M a r g a r e t   C r o n i n   F i s k
-- 2012-04-04T19:23:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-04/new-orleans-police-officers-sentenced-for-post-katrina-deaths.html
Four New Orleans police officers
were sentenced to 38 to 65 years in prison for convictions
including violating the civil rights of two people killed a week
after Hurricane Katrina devastated the city in 2005.  A fifth officer was sentenced to six years for covering up
the crimes.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Margaret Cronin Fisk in Detroit at 
 mcfisk@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Dunn at 
 adunn8@bloomberg.net  